133
00:09:33,050 --> 00:09:34,530
He wants to convene a parliament,

134
00:09:34,530 --> 00:09:35,900
restructure the cabinet,

135
00:09:35,900 --> 00:09:37,140
lift the ban on political parties,

136
00:09:37,140 --> 00:09:38,450
show leniency toward the revolutionaries,

137
00:09:38,450 --> 00:09:40,910
and hold full military command at the front.

138
00:09:42,020 --> 00:09:42,810
Isn't this

139
00:09:42,810 --> 00:09:45,610
the stance of someone
aiming to remake the nation?

140
00:09:45,650 --> 00:09:47,770
Yuan Shikai's ambitions

141
00:09:48,530 --> 00:09:49,770
are as clear as day.

142
00:09:54,140 --> 00:09:56,070
What about His Highness's stance?

143
00:09:58,050 --> 00:09:59,410
I just heard

144
00:10:00,260 --> 00:10:02,200
that he's already looking for someone

145
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:04,130
to draft a rescript for penitence.

146
00:10:07,450 --> 00:10:09,310
Drafting a rescript of penitence

147
00:10:09,380 --> 00:10:10,650
at a time like this?

148
00:10:14,530 --> 00:10:16,660
He's completely lost his initiative.

149
00:10:17,170 --> 00:10:18,970
He took all the blame on himself.

150
00:10:19,050 --> 00:10:20,380
That might show good character, but...

151
00:10:20,380 --> 00:10:21,020
Bullshit!

152
00:10:22,930 --> 00:10:25,660
What's the point of
talking about character now?

153
00:10:26,450 --> 00:10:27,340
If he doesn't step up

154
00:10:27,340 --> 00:10:29,380
right now, who else will?

155
00:10:30,170 --> 00:10:33,370
